      <hedline>
        <hl1>ECONOMIC AID FOR PHILIPPINES</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Wayne Arnold</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Arnold, Wayne</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>International donors pledged $6.2 billion in additional economic aid to Philippines, bringing to $10.3 billion total loans available to country's cash-short government; group, headed by World Bank and Japan, allocated $361 million to promote development projects on southern island of Mindanao (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>International donors pledged $2.6 billion in additional economic aid to the Philippines, bringing to $10.3 billion the total loans available to the country's cash-short government. The group, headed by the World Bank and includes Japan, allocated $361 million to promote development projects on the southern island of Mindanao. The government recently intensified its campaign to quell a Muslim insurgency on Mindanao.</p>
        <p>Wayne Arnold</p>
      </block>
